    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given block diagram is,</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyy5oqdg/cdc3826e-bb07-41a8-9d2b-bb1318217dbc/dc5be440-48cd-11ef-9c03-5b7518daaafa/file-jaoe38c1lyy5oqdh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyy5oqdg/cdc3826e-bb07-41a8-9d2b-bb1318217dbc/dc5be440-48cd-11ef-9c03-5b7518daaafa/file-jaoe38c1lyy5oqdh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2023 Control Systems - Block Diagram and Signal Flow Graph Question 3 English Explanation\">\n\n<p>By Mason's gain formula,</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\frac{Y(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{P_1 \\Delta_1+P_2 \\Delta_2}{\\Delta} \\\\\\\\ &amp; P_1=3 \\quad P_2=\\frac{2}{s} \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\Delta_1=1 \\quad \\Delta_2=1 \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\Delta=1-\\frac{1}{s} \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\frac{Y(\\mathrm{~s})}{R(\\mathrm{~s})}=\\frac{3+\\frac{2}{s}}{1-\\frac{1}{s}}=\\frac{3 s+2}{s-1} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (B).</p>",
