    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh5z26g1/fd3cd1a1-6531-4041-955c-9008819b3cc6/1c67b020-b176-11f0-a8fc-1beb57a635e8/file-jaoe38c1mh5z26g2.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh5z26g1/fd3cd1a1-6531-4041-955c-9008819b3cc6/1c67b020-b176-11f0-a8fc-1beb57a635e8/file-jaoe38c1mh5z26g2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2021 Control Systems - Block Diagram and Signal Flow Graph Question 1 English Explanation\">Closed loop transfer function for negative feedback system is given by,</p>\n<p>$$ \\frac{C(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{G}{1+G H} \\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,...(i)$$</p>\n<p>From the figure, $E(s)$ is input to $G$ and $C(s)$ is output of $G$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\frac{C(s)}{E(s)}=G \\\\ &amp; C(s)=G E(s) \\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,...(ii)\\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>From equation (i) and (ii),</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\frac{G E(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{G}{1+G H} \\\\ &amp; \\frac{E(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{1}{1+G H} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (C).</p>",
